Package org.action.registration

Class Register

java.lang.Object
org.action.registration.Register
public class Register extends Object
A registration connects officer to a project with a specific status (NIL, PENDING, APPROVED, REJECTED) and tracks important dates.

  • Constructor Details

    • Register

      public Register(String registrationID, String userID, String username, String projectID, Register.RegistrationStatus status, String openingDate, String closingDate)
      Constructs a new Registration with the specified details.
      Parameters:
      registrationID - Unique ID for this registration
      userID - ID of the user submitting the registration
      username - Username of the user submitting the registration
      projectID - Project ID being registered for
      status - Current status of the registration
      openingDate - Date when the registration was opened
      closingDate - Date when the registration was closed

  • Method Details

      Provides a string representation of the registration.
      Returns:

    • view_full

      public String view_full()
      Provides a string representation of the registration.
      Returns:
      String containing registration ID, username, and submission date

    • approveRegistration

      public void approveRegistration()
      Approves pending registration. Changes status to APPROVED if current status is PENDING.

    • rejectRegistration

      public void rejectRegistration()
      Rejects a pending registration. Changes status to REJECTED and sets closing date to current date if status is PENDING.

    • filter

      public boolean filter(String userID, String username, String projectID, String registrationID, List<Register.RegistrationStatus> statusWhitelist)
      Filters registrations based on specified criteria.
      Parameters:
      userID - User ID to filter by (empty string to ignore)
      username - Username to filter by (empty string to ignore)
      projectID - Project ID to filter by (empty string to ignore)
      registrationID - Registration ID to filter by (empty string to ignore)
      statusWhitelist - List of statuses to include in the filter
      Returns:
      true if the registration matches all specified criteria, false otherwise
